From: "Jeremy Pollack" <jpollack@...>

Yep.

I don't tend to have a lot of time these days for extra-curricular EQ
activities (ie EQ is fun but losing its luster so I don't use free time as
much to do EQ-stuff. =D) but I still play.

According to onelist we still have 116 members, who knows how many of those
are/were email addies made just for the list though.

So how is everyone doing? How many of you have reached 50 these days?

Personally, Virten is still chugging along rp'ing first, getting exp second,
and just got level 36. And yes I've been playing since release.

How about anyone else? Got anything to share?

later all
virten
aka jeremy
